obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12026)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12026&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with`
  line `Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f`
  line `31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12027)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12027&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires--`
  line
  line `(a) "autism" means a condition of uneven skill development primarily affecting the`
  line `communication and social abilities of a person, marked by repetitive and ritualistic behaviour;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means Board of trustees constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "cerebral palsy" means a group of non-progressive conditions of a person characterised by`
  line `abnormal motor control and posture resulting from brain insult or injuries occurring in the pre-natal,`
  line `perinatal or infant period of development;`
  line
  line `(d) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board appointed under clause (a) of sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) "Chief Executive Officer" means the Chief Executive Officer appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) "Member" means a Member of the Board and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(g) "mental retardation" means a condition of arrested or incomplete development of mind of a`
  line `person which is specially characterised by sub-normality of intelligence;`
  line
  line `(h) "multiple disabilities" means a combination of two or more disabilities as defined in clause (i)`
  line `of section 2 of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full`
  line `Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(j)" persons with disability" means a person suffering from any of the conditions relating to`
  line `autism, cerebral palsy, mental retardation or a combination of any two or more of such conditions and`
  line `includes a person suffering from severe multiple disability;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "professional" means a person who is having special expertise in a field which would promote`
  line `the welfare of persons with disability;`
  line
  line `(m) "registered organisation" means an association of persons with disability or an association of`
  line `parents of persons with disability or a voluntary organisation, as the case may be, registered under`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(n) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "severe disability" means disability with eighty per cent. or more of one or more multiple`
  line disabilities;
  line
  line `(p) "Trust" means the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disability constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12028)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disability, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12028&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint there shall be constituted, for the purposes of this Act, a body`
  line `by the name of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disabilities, which shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having`
  line `perpetual succession and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire,`
  line `hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name,`
  line `sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and business of the Trust`
  line `shall vest in a Board which may exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or`
  line `done by the Trust.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Trust shall be at New Delhi and the Board may, with the previous approval`
  line `of the Central Government, establish offices at other places in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst the persons having`
  line `expertise and experience in the field of autism, cerebral palsy, mental retardation and multiple`
  line disability;
  line
  line `(b) nine persons to be appointed in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed from`
  line `amongst the registered organisations out of which three members each shall be from voluntary`
  line `organisations, association of parents of persons with autism, cerebral palsy, mental retardation and`
  line `multiple disability and from association of persons with disability, Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that initial appointment under this clause shall be made by the Central Government by`
  line nomination;
  line
  line `(c) eight persons not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India nominated by`
  line `that Government to represent the Ministries or Departments of Social Justice and Empowerment,`
  line `Women and Child Development, Health and Family Welfare, Finance, Labour, Education, Urban`
  line `Affairs and Employment and Rural Employment and Poverty Alleviation, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) three Persons to be nominated by the Board representing the associations of trade, commerce`
  line `and industry engaged in philanthropic activities, Members;`
  line
  line `(e) The Chief Executive Officer, who, shall be of the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government`
  line `of India, Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined`
  line `by regulations, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire for carrying out the objects of the`
  line `Trust:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall have a right to take part in the discussions relevant to that purposes`
  line `but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting of the Board and shall not be a member for any other`
  line `purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the maximum number of persons so associated shall not exceed eight and so far`
  line `as possible the person so associated shall belong to the registered organisation or from the professionals`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12029)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members, meeting of Board, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12029&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or a`
  line `Member shall hold office for a term of three years from the date of his appointment ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Chairperson or other Member after he has attained the`
  line `age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Central Government shall initiate the process for appointment of the Chairperson or`
  line `Member, as the case may be, at least six months prior to the expiry of the term of office of such`
  line `Chairperson or Member.]`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions of service of the Chairperson and other Members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) A casual vacancy in the Board shall be filled in accordance with the provisions of section 3 and a`
  line `person appointed shall hold office only for the remainder of the term for which the member, in whose`
  line `place he was appointed, would have held that office:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the Central Government may, in case of a casual vacancy in the office of the`
  line `Chairperson, by order in writing, direct an officer of appropriate level, to perform the functions of the`
  line `Chairperson until such vacancy is filled in.]`
  line
  line `(4) Before appointing any person as the Chairperson or a Member, the Central Government shall`
  line `satisfy itself that the person does not and will not, have any such financial or other interest as is likely to`
  line `affect prejudicially his functions as such Member.`
  line
  line `(5) No Member of the Board shall be a beneficiary of the Trust during the period such Member holds`
  line office.
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall meet at least once in three months at such time and place as may be determined`
  line `by the Board by regulations and shall observe such rules of procedure in the transaction of business at a`
  line `meeting as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson, if for any reason is unable to attend the meeting of the Board, any Member`
  line `elected by the Members present from amongst themselves at the meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(8) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the Members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in`
  line `his absence, the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or until his successor shall have been duly appointed, whichever is longer" omitted by Act 35 of 2018, s. 2,`
  line `(w.e.f 29.12.2018)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 2018, s. 2, (w.e.f. 29.12.2018).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid (w.e.f. 29.12.2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12030)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Resignation of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12030&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may resign his office by`
  line `writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall continue in office ^1[until the appointment of his successor is made`
  line `by the Central Government].`
  line
  line `(2) A Member may resign from office by writing under his hand addressed to the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3 ibid, for the words "until the appointment of his successor is made by the Central Government"`
  line `(w.e.f 29.12.2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12031)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12031&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be a Member if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or becomes, of unsound mind or is so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(b) is, or has been, convicted of an offence, which in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated as an insolvent.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12032)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacation of office by Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12032&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If a member--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 6; or`
  line
  line `(b) is, without obtaining leave of absence, absent from three consecutive meetings of the Board;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) tenders his resignation under section 5,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12033)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Chief Executive Officer and staff of Trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12033&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the direction of the Board as`
  line `may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall, with the previous approval of the Central Government, appoint such other`
  line `officers and employees as it considers necessary to carry out the objectives of the Trust.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, other officers and employees of the Trust shall be such as may be determined by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12034)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies in Board not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12034&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Board shall be`
  line `called in question on the grounds merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the`
  line `constitution of, the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12035)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Objects of Trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12035&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Trust shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to enable and empower persons with disability to live as independently and as fully as`
  line `possible within and as close to the community to which they belong;`
  line
  line `(b) to strengthen facilities to provide support to persons with disability to live within their own`
  line families;
  line
  line `(c) to extend support to registered organisations to provide need based services during the period`
  line `of crisis in the family of persons with disability;`
  line
  line `(d) to deal with problems of persons with disability who do not have family support;`
  line
  line `(e) to promote measures for the care and protection of persons with disability in the event of`
  line `death of their parent or guardian;`
  line
  line `(f) to evolve procedure for the appointment of guardians and trustees for persons with disability`
  line `requiring such protection;`
  line
  line `(g) to facilitate the realisation of equal opportunities, protection of rights and full participation of`
  line `persons with disability; and`
  line
  line `(h) to do any other act which is incidental to the aforesaid objects.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12036)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers and duties of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12036&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall--`
  line
  line `(a) receive from the Central Government a one-time contribution of rupees one hundred crores`
  line `for a corpus, the income whereof shall be utilised to provide for adequate standard of living for`
  line `persons with disability;`
  line
  line `(b) receive bequests of movable property from any person for the benefit of the persons with`
  line `disability in general and for furtherance of the objectives of the Trust in particular:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be obligatory on the part of the Board to make arrangement for adequate`
  line `standard of living for the beneficiary named in the bequest, if any, and to utilise the property`
  line `bequeathed for any other purpose for which the bequest has been made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall not be under any obligation to utilise the entire amount`
  line `mentioned in the bequest for the exclusive benefit of the persons with disability named as beneficiary`
  line `in the bequest;`
  line
  line `(c) receive from the Central Government such sums as may be considered necessary in each`
  line `financial year for providing financial assistance to registered organisations for carrying out any`
  line `approved programme.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the expression "approved programme" means--`
  line
  line `(a) any programme which promotes independent living in the community for persons with`
  line `disability by--`
  line
  line `(i) creating a conducive environment in the community;`
  line
  line `(ii) counselling and training of family members of persons with disability;`
  line
  line `(iii) setting up of adult training units, individual and group homes;`
  line
  line `(b) any programme which promotes respite care, foster family care or day care service for persons`
  line `with disability;`
  line
  line `(c) setting up of residential hostels and residential homes for persons with disability;`
  line
  line `(d) development of self-help groups of persons with disability to pursue the realisation of their`
  line rights;
  line
  line `(e) setting up of local level committee to grant approval for guardianship; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other programmes which promote the objectives of the Trust.`
  line
  line `(3) While earmarking funds for the purposes of clause (c) of sub-section (2), preference shall be given`
  line `to women with disability or to persons with severe disability and to senior citizens with disability.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression,--`
  line
  line `(a) "persons with severe disability" shall have the same meaning as is assigned to it under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 56 of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of`
  line `Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(b) "senior citizen" means a person who is above the age of sixty-five years or more.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12037)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12037&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any association of persons with disability, or any association`
  line `of parents of persons with disability or a voluntary organisation whose main object is promotion of`
  line `welfare of persons with disability may make an application for registration to the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for registration shall be made in such form and manner and at such place as the`
  line `Board may by regulation provide and shall contain such particulars and accompanied with such`
  line `documents and such fees as may be provided in the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of application for registration, the Board may make such enquiries as it thinks fit in`
  line `respect of genuineness of the application and correctness of any particulars thereon.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon receipt of such application the Board shall either grant registration to the applicant or reject`
  line `such application for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that where registration has been refused to the applicant, the said applicant may again make`
  line `an application for registration after removing defects, if any, in its previous application.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12038)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Constitution of local level committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12038&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall constitute a local level committee`
  line `for such area as may be specified by it from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) A local level committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) an officer of the civil service of the Union or of the State, not below the rank of a District`
  line `Magistrate or a District Commissioner of a district;`
  line
  line `(b) a representative of a registered organisation; and`
  line
  line `(c) a person with disability as defined in clause (t) of section 2 of the Persons with Disabilities`
  line `(Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(3) A local level committee shall continue to work for a period of three years from the date of its`
  line `constitution or till such time it is reconstituted by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) A local level committee shall meet at least once in every three months or at such interval as may`
  line `be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12039)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment for guardianship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12039&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A parent of a person with disability or his relative may`
  line `make an application to the local level committee for appointment of any person of his choice to act as a`
  line `guardian of the persons with disability.`
  line
  line `(2) Any registered organisation may make an application in the prescribed form to the local level`
  line `committee for appointment of a guardian for a person with disability:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall be entertained by the local level committee, unless the consent`
  line `of the guardian of the disabled person is also obtained.`
  line
  line `(3) While considering the application for appointment of a guardian, the local level committee shall`
  line consider--
  line
  line `(a) whether the person with disability needs a guardian;`
  line
  line `(b) the purposes for which the guardianship is required for person with disability.`
  line
  line `(4) The local level committee shall receive, process and decide applications received under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2), in such manner as may be determined by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that while making recommendation for the appointment of a guardian, the local level`
  line `committee shall provide for the obligations which are to be fulfilled by the guardian.`
  line
  line `(5) The local level committee shall send to the Board the particulars of the applications received by it`
  line `and orders passed thereon at such interval as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12040)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duties of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12040&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every person appointed as a guardian of a person with disability under this`
  line `Chapter shall, wherever required, either have the care of such person of disability and his property or be`
  line `responsible for the maintenance of the person with disability.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12041)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Guardian to furnish inventory and annual accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12041&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person appointed as a`
  line `guardian under section 14 shall, within a period of six months from the date of his appointment, deliver to`
  line `the authority which appointed him, an inventory of immovable property belonging to the person with`
  line `disability and all assets and other movable property received on behalf of the person with disability,`
  line `together with a statement of all claims due to and all debts and liabilities due by such person with`
  line disability.
  line
  line `(2) Every guardian shall also furnish to the said appointing authority within a period of three months`
  line `at the close of every financial year, an account of the property and assets in his charge, the sums received`
  line `and disbursed on account of the person with disability and the balance remaining with him.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12042)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Removal of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12042&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a parent or a relative of a person with disability or a`
  line `registered organisation finds that the guardian is--`
  line
  line `(a) abusing or neglecting a person with disability; or`
  line
  line `(b) misappropriating or neglecting the property,`
  line
  line `it may in accordance with the prescribed procedure apply to the committee for the removal of such`
  line guardian.
  line
  line `(2) Upon receiving such application the committee may, if it is satisfied that there is a ground for`
  line `removal and for reasons to be recorded in writing, remove such guardian and appoint a new guardian in`
  line `his place or if such a guardian is not available make such other arrangements as may be necessary for the`
  line `care and protection of person with disability.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person removed under sub-section (2) shall be bound to deliver the charge of all property of`
  line `the person with disability to the new guardian, and to account for all moneys received or disbursed by`
  line him.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "relative" includes any person related`
  line `to the person with disability by blood, marriage or adoption.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12043)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Accountability.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12043&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The books and documents in the possession of the Board shall be open to`
  line `inspection by any registered organisation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any registered organisation can submit a written requisition to the Board for getting a copy of any`
  line `book or document maintained by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall frame such regulations as it thinks necessary for allowing the access of any book`
  line `or document to a registered organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12044)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Monitoring.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12044&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall determine by regulations the procedure for evaluating the`
  line `prefunding status of registered organisations seeking financial assistance from it and such regulations may also provide for the guidelines for monitoring and evaluating the activities of the registered organisations`
  line `who are receiving financial assistance from the Trust`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12045)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12045&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall in each year hold an annual general meeting of`
  line `registered organisations, and not more than six months shall elapse between the date of one annual`
  line `general meeting and that of the next.`
  line
  line `(2) A notice of the annual general meeting along with a statement of accounts and records of its`
  line `activities during the preceding year shall be sent by the Board to every registered organisation at such`
  line `time as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The quorum of such meeting shall be such number of persons of the registered organisations as`
  line `may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12046)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12046&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made be Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Trust a one-time contribution of rupees one`
  line `hundred crores for a corpus, the income whereof may be utilised to achieve the objects of the Trust under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12047)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Fund.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12047&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the National Trust for Welfare of`
  line `Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Fund and there shall`
  line `be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys received from the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys received by the Trust by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `and transfers;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Trust in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `the Board may, subject to the approval of the Central Government, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Funds shall be applied towards meeting the administrative and other expenses of the Trust`
  line `including expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and performance of duties by the Board in`
  line `relation to any of its activities under section 10 or for anything relatable thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12048)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12048&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may be`
  line `prescribed, the budget for the next financial year showing the estimated receipt and expenditure of the`
  line `Trust and shall forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12049)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12049&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts of the Trust including the income and expenditure accounts`
  line `in such form as the Central Government may prescribe and in accordance with such general direction as`
  line `may be issued by that Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Trust shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such`
  line `audit shall be payable by Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Trust shall have the same rights, privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books of account, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any`
  line `of the offices of the Trust.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Trust as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government, and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12050)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12050&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare every year, in such form and within such time as may`
  line `be prescribed an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12051)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Authentication of orders, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12051&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the Board and instruments issued in`
  line `the name of the Trust shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairperson, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer or any other officer authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12052)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Returns and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12052&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall furnish to the Central Government such reports,`
  line `returns and other information as that Government may require from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12053)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12053&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Board shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its duties under this`
  line `Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to`
  line `it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12054)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12054&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government on the`
  line `complaint of a registered organisation or otherwise has reason to believe that the Board is unable to`
  line `perform or has persistently made default in the performance of the duties imposed on it, the Central`
  line `Government may issue notice to the Board asking why it should not be superseded:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order superseding the Board shall be made by the Central Government, unless a`
  line `notice affording reasonable opportunity to the Board has been given in writing that why it should not be`
  line superseded.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government after recording reasons in writing and by issuing a notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette supersede the Board for a period of not more than six months:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the expiration of the period of supersession, the Central Government may`
  line `reconstitute the Board, in accordance with section 3.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon the publication of the notification under sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members of the Board shall, notwithstanding that their term of office had not expired as`
  line `on the date of supersession, vacate their office as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of the Trust shall, during the period of supersession, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (2), the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further period as it may consider necessary so that`
  line `the total period of supersession does not exceed more than six months; or`
  line
  line `(b) reconstitute the Board in the manner provided in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12055)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Exemption from tax on income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12055&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961), or any other law for the time being in force relating to tax on income, profits or gains,`
  line `the Trust shall not be liable to pay income-tax or any other tax in respect of its income, profits or gains`
  line derived.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12056)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12056&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the Trust or any member of the Board or Chief Executive Officer or`
  line `any officer or other employee of the Trust or any other person authorised by the Board to perform duties`
  line `under this Act for any loss or damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is done in good`
  line faith.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "good faith" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as is assigned to it in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12057)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Chairperson, Members and officers of Trust to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12057&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `All Members, Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, other officers and employees of the Trust shall be deemed, when acting or purporting`
  line `to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servant within the meaning of section`
  line `21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12058)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12058&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the Chairperson`
  line `or any member or any officer of the Trust or any other person subject to such conditions and limitations,`
  line `if any, as may be specified in the order such of its powers under this Act (except the power to make`
  line `regulations under section 35) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12059)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12059&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure in accordance with which the persons representing registered organisation shall`
  line `be elected under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the rules of procedure in the transaction of business at meetings of the Board under`
  line `sub- section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and duties of the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which an application for guardianship may be made by a registered organisation`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure in accordance with which a guardian may be removed under section 17;`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which, and the time within which, the budget of the Trust shall be forwarded to`
  line `the Central Government under section 23;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be maintained under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 24;`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which, and the time within which, the annual reports shall be prepared and`
  line `forwarded under section 25;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12060)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12060&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and rules`
  line `generally to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner and purpose for which a person may be associated under sub-section (5) of section`
  line 3;
  line
  line `(b) the time and place at which the Board shall meet under sub-section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of service of, Chief Executive Officer, other officers and employees`
  line `of the Trust under sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner in which the application shall be made for registration under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 12 and the particulars which such application shall contain under that`
  line sub-section;
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which application for guardianship shall be received, processed and decided by`
  line `the local level committee under sub-section (4) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) the particulars of applications and orders passed thereon by the local level committee under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure for evaluating the pre-funding status of the registered organisations and framing`
  line `of guidelines for monitoring and evaluating the activities of such registered organisations under`
  line `section 19;`
  line
  line `(h) the time within which notice for annual general meeting shall be sent and quorum for such`
  line `meeting under sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 20; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, provided by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12061)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315&sectionId=12061&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00004_199944_1517807323315
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `राष्ट्री य स्वकपरायणता, प्रमस्तियष्क् घात, मानसिक मंदता औरबहु-नि:शक्तयताग्रस्ति व्य्क्ति् कल्यातण न्यातसअधिनियम, 1999`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/1951/2/H1999-44.pdf`
